                <p>A bicycle tour or expedition that prioritizes fun, exploration, and discovery is sometimes called a "bike adventure." Exploring new locations and immersing oneself in the environment entails riding a bicycle throughout various terrains, including urban landscapes, rural roads, mountain trails, and seaside walks. The growing number of bike-friendly facilities in cities in the United States has contributed to this trend as legislators and urban planners see the advantages of encouraging riding as a practical form of transportation.</p>
